summary: This is an FBI shipping invoice detailing the transfer of original and derivative evidence, including numerous hard drives and a DVR system, from the FBI's Engineering Research Facility in Quantico, VA, to the FBI's New York Field Office. The evidence is related to the death investigation of Jeffrey Epstein, who is listed as the victim.

events.title: Evidence Transfer to FBI New York
events.description: The FBI's Engineering Research Facility in Quantico, VA, shipped a large collection of digital evidence, including original and cloned hard drives and a DVR system, to the FBI's New York Field Office for the Jeffrey Epstein death investigation.

locations: FEDERAL BUREAU OF INVESTIGATION BLDG 27958A QUANTICO, VA 22135
FBI - New York 26 Federal Plaza New York, NY 10278
ENGINEERING RESEARCH FACILITY BUILDING 27958-A QUANTICO, VA 22135
keyFacts: The document is an evidence shipping invoice from the FBI's Engineering Research Facility to the FBI's New York Field Office.
The evidence transferred includes a DVR system and at least 18 original hard drives, plus numerous cloned derivative hard drives.
The case is identified as '090A-NY-3151227-58-1' and titled 'UNSUB(S); JEFFREY EPSTEIN - VICTIM; DEATH INVESTIGATION'.
The document confirms the FBI was actively processing digital evidence related to Jeffrey Epstein's death investigation as of September 2020.
The evidence was shipped via Federal Express on September 24, 2020.
